    "body": "I'm okay with something like `DEFAULT_EMPTY_FLAGS`. These are bitflags that should be able to be set and unset. By initializing it to something non-integer, we don't have the ability to simply flip a bit to turn on a flag. Also beacuse `ValidatorRecord` is a state object, we need to keep this field defined wrt it's SSZ types. so `None` is a non-starter.\r\n\r\nthe next flags defined (if they do become defined) would be at `4`, `8`, `16,` etc for each subsequent bit",
